name: BP Simply food

directions: Get key from the cutting counter. Bathroom is against the back wall in a small hallway.

name: Coffee Culture

name: Farinacci Pizza
comment: Generally for customers

name: Grace Church
directions: top floor across from café
comment: open most daytime hours just walk in and act like you know what you're doing.... also it's a church so people might give you weird looks but no one would actually say anything.... anyway not ideal but if you can deal with that it works

name: Grace Church
directions: top floor across from café
comment: open most daytime hours just walk in and act like you know what you're doing.... also it's a church so people might give you weird looks but no one would actually say anything.... anyway not ideal but if you can deal with that it works

name: Great Bay Community College
directions: Facing the south entrance or next to the Green Bean.

name: Walmart Supercenter
directions:
Located in the back of the store under a bright orange sign that says "Pickup Here"
There's a men's restroom on the right, women's on the left, and family in the middle
comment: Family restroom. It's spacious, locks, and has a mirror ;)

name: Starbucks
directions: The store & bathrooms are ADA/accessible, but shopping center has a curbed sidewalk. Access ramp is at the center of the shopping center, away from the Starbucks.
comment: It's always pretty busy here.

name: UMSL Rec Center
street: 229 Recreation and Wellness Center, 1 University Boulevard
directions: On the main level there are two single stall restrooms without gender labels. These are by the vending machines in the public space (not past the turn stiles). On the first floor there is a gender neutral locker room by the pool.
comment: To get to the locker room you need to be a guest of a patron or a patron. Anyone can use the gender neutral restrooms on the main level.

name: Target
directions: When you first walk in turn right
comment: Family bathroom

name: Aldi Grocery Store
directions:
ROUTE 1/SHORTCUT ROUTE: After you enter through the front doors, immediately turn right(walking in front of the bench) and then pass through an empty checkout lane, it should be directly in front of you, through a doorway directly next to the checkout lanes.
ROUTE 2/REGULAR ROUTE: Walk straight after entering the store, down the first aisle. Turn right, walk straight back to the far wall, take another right, and once you get to the checkout lanes the bathrooms should be on your left.

name: The Hideaway Café
directions: The hideaway is kind of hard to find itself, when you find the sign go in the doors, turn left and go through those doors, and go down the stairs.
comment: Everyone there is super nice. You probably don't have to be a paying customer but it never hurts to be just in case. The bathrooms are gendered but there are signs up that say to use the bathroom that suits your personal identification. Super safe space.

name: Central Park Dance
comment: Friendly staff, would be welcoming.

name: Murray Hall
directions: In the basement around the corner from the elevator. Take elevator to floor 0 (not 00), make a left, walk through a doorway then make a right. The bathroom is on your right. There is one grab bar for accessibility but no push button for the door. The hand dryer is also location in a high place.
comment: A little confusing to get to, but rarely in use. Near the computer lab and office 031.

name: Children's Room at the Reuben Hoar Library
directions: go into the main entrance and walk to the front desk turn left and the stairs will be on the left. go all the way up open the door into the children's section. turn to the right and walk to the end of the room and into the area that has like the children's toys and stuff and there is a unisex single stall that locks. it is a good sized room with one toilet, one sink with a mirror above it, and a baby changing station.
comment: just walk at a normal pace and act natural like you're going to get a book. all of the librarians are very kind and some of them either are or have children who are a part of the LGBT+ community

name: St Mary of the Falls
directions: Enter parking lot from Bagley Rd, just north of Columbia. The left set of doors (there are three) are the ones you want. After entering church, go up slant to the right and then turn right after going through the doorway. There are two gender-neutral bathrooms in the hall.
comment: Be mindful that this is a church. They are, however, pretty progressive and you'll be welcome. The doors are open for only a portion of time every day - I would recommend using this as a backup if you can't find anything else local.

name: Ledding Library
directions: Next to the entrance on the main floor
comment: Open to the public

name: Snow College Suites at Academy Square
directions: First floor next to reception desk thing.
comment: The Suites are locked but if you knock on the door someone will let you in. Just pretend you left your key up in your room.

name: Superior Building
directions: On 1st floor, closer to Rockwell road entrance
comment: Building doors open 7am-6pm EST

name: Fernweh inn and hostel
directions: On first floor by kitchen. If you are a guest, there is also a gender neutral dorm and restroom upstairs, as well as private rooms.
comment: Just ask management nicely to use the restroom. They are great folks. Maybe ask for a tour of the hostel while you're there!

name: Lowe's
directions: Front wall behind the cashiers, labeled "family restroom"

name: Lovejoy United Presbyterian Church
directions: Through the front enterance, down the hall past the book shelves and through the door on the left. It's a single-stall restroom.
comment: The members of this church are very friendly, welcoming, and understanding. This is a safe place for trans/nb people

name: Rondo Library
directions: At the entrance. Need to get a key from the front desk.

name: Todds Tasties
comment: Only for customers

name: Hamline University Drew Science Center
directions: Second floor

name: Optimism Brewery

comment: The stalls are divided by toilets and urinals. Each is private and handwashing is communal. The bathroom of the future.

name: Tibetan Kitchen
directions: Single bathroom establishment.

name: Lovejoy United Presbyterian Church
directions: I you go through the front enterenace, it's down the hall and through the door to left. It's a single-stall restroom.
comment: Members of this church are very welcoming, friendly, and understanding. This church is a very safe place for trans/non-conforming/non-binary people

name: Teddy's
directions: Take a left to the hallway, and bathrooms are on the right.
comment: It's a restaurant, but they will probably let you use the bathroom even if you're not a customer.

name: Hamline University Anderson Center
directions: Second floor in the back. Marked family restroom.

name: Luc Lac
directions: All the way in the back of the restaurant by the kitchen
comment: Place is usually busy so you could just walk back there. Is accessible -  but is crowded - so getting back there may be challenging

name: BCEC Boston Convention and Exhibition Center
directions: In the North lobby (Summer St entrance), on either side. Between the gendered bathrooms.
comment: Before the ticket counter so it's probably reachable without a hassle, depending on the event and if they're open.

name: Hamline University Drew Hall
directions: Second floor in residence area
comment: You will need a key card to access or a friend with one to take you there.

name: Soft Spot Bar
directions: Back on the left.
comment: It's a bar, but folks are friendly.

name: Milwaukee Institute of Art and Design
directions: Bottom floor, take a left at the grand staircase and follow the hallway. After the art gallery but before the cafe.
comment: Pretend you're a student who's been in the building a thousand times.

name: IKEA
directions: Right when you walk in, behind the main display of the entrance

name: Grace Church of Overland Park
directions: across from café area
comment: open most typical working hours.... just like say hi to the secretary or something and act like you know what you're doing

name: Bean and Leaf Café

comment: A 10/10 cup of coffee :)

name: Lake Harriet United Methodist Church
directions: Down the stairs to the right when you enter the building. Turn left at the bottom of the stairs.
comment: It is a church, but they are a community that affirms people of all genders.

name: Bean and Leaf Café

comment: A 10/10 cup of coffee :)

name: Tabletop Game Cafe

name: Vandegrift Highschool
directions: It's in the second building across from the cafeteria, usually open during school days and public events.
comment: It's marked as a family restroom, and has a het couple with a child on it which is gross.

name: Arcata Pizza Deli
directions: Two neutral bathrooms. Down the hall on the right side of the order counter.

name: Grand Forks International Airport

name: Midori's Floating World Cafe

comment: LGBTQ+ friendly clinic. Under 25 probably preferred (they're age based) but I don't think they'd refuse someone who needed to use the bathroom.

name: Acre Coffee

comment: don't have to be a paying customer but be sly about it the staff might be annoyed by constant bathroom-only use

name: Reed's laundry mat and dry cleaning
directions: If you enter the laundry mat you will see rows of washers. To the far right by the folding tables there are two huge 60 pound washers we call 'big boys' behind them there is about two feet untill the wall. There's a door there to the gender neutral single stall bathroom. Currently the lock is broken but the door can be reached from the toilet so you can comfortably hold it closed while in there. We should be fixing the lock soon.
comment: You don't need to be washing any clothes to use the restoom. It's on the opposit wall from the employee area so you won't likely even encounter someone who works there I'd you choose to use it. I'm (Theo Ira) a trans employee there and you'll have an alli too.

name: Ashkers juice bar
directions: As soon as you enter through the front door you will see the counter ahead of you. To the left through one arch way (still visible) is a single stall any gender restroom.
comment: I don't believe you need to be a paying costumer but Ashkers is a great local business with delicious teas and smoothies so if your into that check it out.

name: Sam's Sorrento Pizza
directions: In the lobby.
comment: Just ask to use the bathroom!

name: Tabletop Game Cafe
directions: In the back, on the right.

name: Hypertext Bookstore

name: Starbucks
